<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 01 at 9:17AM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...An area of lake effect snow showers will affect southwestern Erie and central
Crawford Counties Until 1015 AM EDT....
At 914 AM EDT, radar indicated a band of snow showers extending from
Lake Erie to near Albion, to Meadville.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Visibility dropping to less than one half mile...
Up to 1 inch of quick snow accumulation...
Locations impacted include...
Meadville, Girard, Cambridge Springs, Albion, Harmonsburg, Guys
Mills, Lake City, Cochranton, Saegertown, Conneautville, Conneaut
Lake, Cranesville, Springboro, Platea, Blooming Valley, Venango,
Woodcock, Conneaut Lakeshore, and Geneva.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
